1.2
log
@introduce another new sysctl: ddb.crash (DBCTL_CRASH)
* default value: 0
* can be set to any other value (CTLTYPE_INT) by the superuser
* setting to value 1 only possible in securelevel 0 and insecure mode
* setting to a value >1 only possible if it was 1 before

this can be used to manually crash the kernel (should be
continuable), but only if enabled before raising securelevel
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
/**	$MirOS$ */
d5 1
d7 7
d23 3
